# Project Structure

## Directory Layout

```
src/
├── server.ts         # Dev server (Bun.serve)
├── preview.ts        # Preview built output
├── index.html        # Entry point
├── app/
│   ├── main.ts       # App bootstrap
│   ├── router.ts     # Navigation/routing logic
│   ├── state.ts      # Minimal state management
│   └── components/   # Reusable UI components
├── content/
│   ├── _graph.ts     # Navigation graph
│   ├── _types.ts     # Content type definitions
│   └── [topic]/      # Topic-grouped content nodes
└── styles/
    ├── base.css      # Reset, typography, variables
    ├── components.css # Component styles
    └── themes.css    # Light/dark theme definitions

docs/
├── DESIGN.md         # Design philosophy
├── CONTENT-GUIDE.md  # How to author content

dist/                 # Built output (gitignored)
```

## Import Conventions

Use path aliases defined in tsconfig.json:
- `@/*` → `src/*`
- `@content/*` → `src/content/*`
- `@components/*` → `src/app/components/*`

## Content Organization

- Group content by topic area (foundations, training, ecosystem, etc.)
- Each `.tsx` file is one content node
- Node file name matches node `id`
- Keep interactive components co-located or in shared components

## Styling

- Use CSS custom properties for all colors, spacing, typography
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Component styles scoped via CSS layers or naming convention
- No CSS-in-JS; keep styles in `.css` files

## Build Output

- Code-split by content node (dynamic imports)
- Prefetch likely next nodes
- Static output suitable for GitHub Pages
- No server-side logic in production
